{"id":48152,"title":"Thyroid disorders and diabetes.","abstract":"Thyroid disorders and diabetes mellitus are two of the most common endocrine conditions, which occur with greater frequency along with each other. This communication describes current knowledge about these twin diseases. Epidemiology, clinical features, laboratory abnormalities, screening and therapeutic implication of this relationship are discussed. The article underlines the clinical relevance of thyroid disorder in diabetes management.","date":"2014-09-25","categories":"Endocrine System Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25252531","annotations":[{"name":"Diabetes mellitus","weight":0.840845,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetes_mellitus"},{"name":"Communication","weight":0.814871,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Communication"},{"name":"Epidemiology","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epidemiology"},{"name":"Endocrine system","weight":0.773888,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endocrine_system"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.701843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Thyroid","weight":0.627397,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thyroid"},{"name":"Laboratory","weight":0.609634,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laboratory"},{"name":"Screening (medicine)","weight":0.57819,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Screening_(medicine)"},{"name":"Clinical psychology","weight":0.386427,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_psychology"},{"name":"Twin","weight":0.122139,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Twin"},{"name":"Management","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management"},{"name":"Knowledge","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedi